         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Provision of 10 Griffon Pinion Gears</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>FAST/00215</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="34731500"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SUPPLIES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Procurement of 10 (ten) new Rolls Royce Griffon Pinion Gears, design standard (including new manufacturing processes) to support the 2 in-service Griffon engines and the 2 spare engines. This buy also provides a spares pool to support the availability of the Battle of Britain Memorial Flight Spitfire XIX aircraft in achieving their display commitment out to their current out of service date of 2035 (in-terms of PG).</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">266000</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>UNITED KINGDOM.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Procurement of 10 (ten) new Rolls Royce Griffon Pinion Gears, design standard (including new manufacturing processes) to support the 2 in-service Griffon engines and the 2 spare engines. This buy also provides a spares pool to support the availability of the Battle of Britain Memorial Flight Spitfire XIX aircraft in achieving their display commitment out to their current out of service date of 2035 (in-terms of PG).</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
                  <AC_PRICE/>
               </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
               <INFO_ADD>
                  <P>This notice is not a request for expressions of interest so please do not apply to be invited to tender. This notice advises that the Authority has decided to negotiate a contract with the named supplier on a single source basis, and is published for reasons of transparency.</P>
               </INFO_ADD>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
               <PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
                  <D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                     <D_TECHNICAL/>
                  </D_ACCORDANCE_ARTICLE>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>Justification for single source.</P>
                     <P>It is considered that for technical reasons, this contract can be placed using the Negotiated Procedure without prior publication of a contract notice pursuant to Article 32 of Directive 2014/24/EU (regulation 32(2)(b)(ii) of the Public Contracts Regulations 2015)..</P>
                     <P>The BBMF Spitfire Mk XIX aircraft use the RG30 SM-S Griffon engine converted from the Mk 58 Griffon. As the Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM) for the Griffon Pinion Gear Rolls Royce PLC have the knowledge on the usage of the original Pinion Gear, its specification and the production / manufacturing methods. Through this OEM knowledge they are the only company who has the data supporting technical information, the ‘design knowhow’, (such as: specific type records; company-owned specifications, engine lifting date) required to understand what design changes are required for the new Pinion Gear. It is essential that the OEM is the designer / manufacturer of the new Pinion Gear as the failure of a Pinion Gear in flight results in the engine stopping; aircraft loses thrust and could potentially lead to loss of life. Any alternative design would be carried out without the necessary historical data available to the OEM, would not be supported or approved by the OEM and introduce a component into the engine not approved for use with the other elements. Given the possible consequences of an engine failure, this presents an unacceptable safety risk to the Authority.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_NEGOTIATED_WITHOUT_PUBLICATION>
            </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
            <NO_CONTRACT_COVERED_GPA/>
         </PROCEDURE>
